The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New York, Aug. 9 (PTI): The body of a homeless Sikh man, stabbed and battered beyond recognition with a broomstick, has been found outside a gurdwara in Richmond, a US city with a large Indian population.          
	Police said the mans features were barely recognisable. The motive is not known and so the police are not treating the murder as a hate crime. The victim apparently used to be a practising Sikh but gave up wearing a turban after turning alcoholic.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Centre on Friday announced a plan to set up a special cell in all states to check circulation of fake currency . The Union home secretarys statement came in the backdrop of the recovery of Rs 1.5 crore in fake notes in a State Bank of India branch in Dumariyaganj in Uttar Pradesh.                   
	 Bulandshahr (PTI): A 20-year-old housewife, allegedly raped by four persons, tore off her clothes on Saturday in a police station accusing police of protecting the rapists.                  
	 Aligarh (PTI): A woman gave birth to a baby outside a rural health centre after she was allegedly denied admission. The baby was rushed to the nearby district hospital, but could not be saved. Rajna Devi, 22, is still in a critical condition. Three staff members have been suspended.                  
	 Kanpur (PTI): Three women died of suffocation on Saturday when a fire broke out after an air-conditioner blast in their house. The fire brigade took more than an hour to control the fire.                   
	 Sirsa (PTI): A labourer accused police of inaction on Saturday saying they were making no efforts to find his two daughters allegedly kidnapped by two masons.                                                                                                                          
